(44, 19, 40, 44, 17, 5, 8, 'uproar', 'Uproar and Public Disturbance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of uproar caused by the spread of new ideas. In Acts 19:40, the concern is about being questioned due to the uproar, while Acts 17:5-8 describes how a similar uproar was instigated by those opposing the message of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 40, 44, 20, 1, 1, 'this day’s uproar', 'Uproar and Resolution', 'This connection highlights the transition from conflict to calm. The ''uproar'' mentioned in both passages signifies a pivotal moment that leads to Paul''s subsequent actions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 40, 44, 21, 31, 31, 'uproar', 'Uproar in Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of uproar, indicating a chaotic situation that poses a threat to the individuals involved. The mention of ''uproar'' in both contexts highlights the societal tensions present in these events.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
