(44, 19, 41, 20, 15, 1, 2, 'dismissed the assembly', 'Wisdom in Speech', 'This connection highlights the importance of how words can influence situations. Acts 19:41 shows the resolution of conflict through dismissal, while Proverbs 15:1-2 emphasizes that a soft answer can prevent anger.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 41, 21, 9, 17, 17, 'dismissed the assembly', 'Wisdom and Authority in Speech', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the dismissal of the assembly in Acts and the quiet wisdom of the wise in Ecclesiastes. Both passages emphasize the effectiveness of wise words over the loudness of foolish authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 41, 47, 1, 8, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Deliverance Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of deliverance from distress. In Acts, the assembly is dismissed, indicating a resolution, while in 2 Corinthians, Paul speaks of being delivered from overwhelming troubles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 1, 44, 19, 21, 21, 'departed for to go into Macedonia', 'Paul''s Journey Plans', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s intention to travel, first to Macedonia and then to Jerusalem. The mention of Macedonia in Acts 19:21 sets the stage for his departure in Acts 20:1.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 1, 47, 7, 5, 5, 'departed for to go into Macedonia', 'Paul''s Journey to Macedonia', 'This connection highlights Paul''s journey into Macedonia, as noted in both passages. Acts 20:1 mentions Paul''s departure for Macedonia, while 2 Corinthians 7:5 describes the challenges he faced upon arrival there.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 1, 54, 1, 3, 3, 'departed for to go into Macedonia', 'Paul''s Journey to Macedonia', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s departure into Macedonia, linking his travels. This connection highlights the continuity of Paul''s mission and the instructions given to Timothy during this journey.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 1, 1, 48, 10, 10, 'embraced them', 'Embracing and Farewell', 'Both passages emphasize the act of embracing loved ones during significant moments. In Acts, Paul embraces the disciples before departing, while in Genesis, Israel embraces his grandsons as he nears the end of his life.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 1, 9, 20, 41, 42, 'departed for to go into Macedonia', 'Farewell and Emotional Bonding', 'This connection highlights the emotional farewells between close companions. Both passages depict intimate moments of parting, emphasizing love and commitment in their relationships.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 1, 44, 11, 26, 26, 'the disciples', 'Paul''s Journey and Discipleship', 'This connection highlights Paul''s role in nurturing disciples, as seen in both passages. In Acts 20:1, Paul embraces the disciples before departing, while in Acts 11:26, he teaches and assembles with the church, emphasizing the importance of community and teaching in the early church.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 1, 45, 16, 16, 16, 'embraced them', 'Connection of Greetings and Fellowship', 'This connection highlights the theme of fellowship among believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of greeting and embracing one another in the Christian community.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 2, 51, 1, 28, 28, 'much exhortation', 'Exhortation and Teaching Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of exhortation and teaching present in both passages. Acts 20:2 mentions ''much exhortation,'' while Colossians 1:28 emphasizes ''warning every man'' and ''teaching every man.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 2, 52, 2, 3, 3, 'much exhortation', 'Exhortation in Paul’s Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of exhortation in both passages. Acts 20:2 mentions Paul''s exhortation to the believers, while 1 Thessalonians 2:3 clarifies the nature of that exhortation as sincere and free from deceit.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 2, 52, 4, 1, 1, 'much exhortation', 'Exhortation and Pleasing God', 'This connection highlights the theme of exhortation present in both passages. Acts 20:2 mentions ''much exhortation,'' while 1 Thessalonians 4:1 uses ''exhort you'' to encourage believers to walk and please God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 2, 44, 20, 11, 11, 'much exhortation', 'Exhortation and Fellowship', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of community and fellowship. In Acts 20:2, the exhortation suggests a gathering, while Acts 20:11 describes a communal meal and extended conversation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 2, 38, 9, 13, 13, 'Greece', 'Connection Between Greece and Judah', 'This connection highlights the mention of Greece in both passages. Acts 20:2 references Greece, while Zechariah 9:13 speaks of Zion''s sons against Greece, suggesting a thematic link between the two contexts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 20, 2, 44, 2, 40, 40, 'much exhortation', 'Exhortation and Salvation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the act of exhortation, with Acts 20:2 highlighting Paul''s encouragement to the believers and Acts 2:40 urging individuals to save themselves. This connection highlights the importance of guidance and the call to action in the early Christian community.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
